Shisomen offers a fusion with Japanese dish and veganism. And I gotta say I totally enjoyed it.

Design wise :
It’s a nice and well set place, subtle, with a feeling of comfy and cozy Japanese touch.

Food wise :
We got to try different appetizers and they were all pretty tasty. I got the shoyu ramen and even though it was not pork, it was still pretty tasty and broth really good.

Cocktail wise :
You gotta try their cocktail especially the Sakura Dream that was for me the best.

Price wise : completely affordable and worth it regarding to the quality and the effort of making vegan food accessible.

Loved the concept and will be back when I’m back in Berlin.

You have to try it !', 'languageCode': 'en'}, 'originalText': {'text': 'A true wonderful surprise !

The service really fast and we were in and out of the restaurant in about 35 minutes.

Meals were between €7-15 per person depending on what was ordered and we didn’t order any drinks this morning. Personally, I had limited options due to a nut allergy but there were a lot of great options if you don’t have that allergy.

It was really interesting inside with all the different bikes. Highly recommend checking it out.', 'languageCode': 'en'}, 'originalText': {'text': 'Walked down the street from our Airbnb to check out this restaurant for breakfast. We were a group of 4 and had about 35-40 minutes before we had to get to a walking tour.

The service really fast and we were in and out of the restaurant in about 35 minutes.
